GOVERNMENT PUBLICATIONS — PUBLIC DOMAIN
----------------------------------------

The assessment objectives, control families, security requirements, and
related compliance content presented in this tool are derived from the
following U.S. Government publications, which are not subject to copyright
in the United States (17 U.S.C. § 105):

  - NIST Special Publication 800-171 Revision 2 & Revision 3
    "Protecting Controlled Unclassified Information in Nonfederal Systems
    and Organizations"

  - NIST Special Publication 800-171A Revision 2 & Revision 3
    "Assessing Security Requirements for Controlled Unclassified Information"

  - NIST Special Publication 800-172 & 800-172A
    "Enhanced Security Requirements for Protecting Controlled Unclassified
    Information" and assessment procedures

  - NIST Special Publication 800-53 Revision 5
    "Security and Privacy Controls for Information Systems and Organizations"

  - CMMC (Cybersecurity Maturity Model Certification) Program materials
    published by the U.S. Department of Defense

  - FedRAMP (Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program) guidance
    and documentation published by the U.S. General Services Administration

Attribution is appreciated by NIST but not legally required for U.S.
Government works.


